<h2>Overview</h2>	
<p>This feature adapts the HTML5 core markup structure for use with Server side   includes (SSI).</p>
<h3>Benefits</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Helps to minimize the duplication of content and code (such as titles and   dates)</li>
  <li>Provides central control of the left and right columns</li>
  <li>Improves consistency by separating content from the template code</li>   
  <li>Automates the breadcrumb trail</li>
  <li>Conforms to WCAG 2.0 AA</li>
  <li>Uses WAI-ARIA to enhance accessibility</li>
  <li>Supports Firefox, Opera, Safari, Chrome, and IE 7+ </li>
</ul>
<h3>Minimum Requirements</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Build folder from WET 3.1.2</li>
  <li>Server Side Includes installed on a web server</li>
</ul>
<h3>How to install the files</h3>
<p>Make sure that you have the WET 3.1.2 build folder in your root directory. Copy the following directories to the root:</p>
<ul>
  <li>inc\</li>
  <li>demos\ssi</li>
  </ul>
<p>"inc" is a folder with your global include files.</p>
<p>Another "inc" folder for page specific includes is under the demos\ssi folder, as well as a folder for main "menu" based includes. Also,shtm pages are located here.</p>
<ul>
  <li>demos\ssi</li>
  <li>demos\ssi\inc</li>
  <li>demos\ssi\menu</li>
  <li>demos\ssi\menu-left-gauche
</li>
</ul>
